Board of Directors



Vicki L. Avril



Hinsdale, Illinois, United States
Director since: 2016
Independent Director
Ms. Avril is a Corporate Director. Ms. Avril retired from IPSCO Tubulars Inc. in 2013 after 9 years, including five years as President and CEO. Prior to 2008, she held progressively senior executive positions with IPSCO Inc., including Senior Vice President of IPSCO Tubulars Operations and Chief Financial Officer of IPSCO Inc. Prior to 2004, Ms. Avril served as Chief Financial Officer for Wallace Computer Services and as a senior officer at Inland Steel Industries in various financial and strategy roles, including Chief Financial Officer, Treasurer, and head of Corporate Planning. Ms. Avril is a director of Commercial Metals Company, Global Brass and Copper Holdings, Inc. and Greif, Inc.
Ms. Avril graduated from the University of Illinois with a Bachelor of Science degree in Accountancy and a Master of Business Administration degree from the University of Chicago.
Ms. Avril is a member and Financial Expert of the Audit Committee and the Safety, Environment & Social Responsibility Committee.








































 





