Executive Profile
Vicki L. Avril  Independent Director, Greif, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 4 Board Members in 4 different organizations across 6 different industries.See Board Relationships63$241,500
Background

		Ms. Vicki L. Avril served as the Chief Executive Officer of TMK IPSCO since June 2008 until 2013 and President since June 2008. Ms. Avril served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of IPSCO Tubulars, Inc. from 2008 to 2013. She served as Chief Financial Officer and Senior Vice President of Evraz IPSCO Inc. from May 2004 to July 19, 2007. She served various positions, including Senior Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of Evraz Inc. NA Canada (formerly, ... IPSCO Inc.). From 2001 to 2003, Ms. Avril served as Chief Financial Officer and Senior Vice President of Wallace Computer Services, Inc. She was deeply involved in the sale of Wallace to Moore Corp., forming MooreWallace, the third largest printing company in the United States. Ms. Avril served as Vice President of Finance and Chief Financial Officer for Inland Steel Industries. Ms. Avril served as Treasurer of Ryerson Tull, Inc. and its subsidiaries of Tull, Ryerson and Inland Steel Industries Inc. (“ISI“), a holding company of Ryerson Tull Inc. since February 1994. She joined ISI in January 1994 and served as its Director of Corporate Planning since January 1995. In addition, she served as Director of Pension Investments and Administration at ISI from June 1991 to January 1995 and Assistant Treasurer of ISI from May 1993 to January 1994. She has 30 years of financial, treasury and accounting management experience, including 23 years in the steel industry. She has substantial experience in the pipe and steel industry and held senior management positions with Inland Steel Industries, Inc. Ms. Avril has been an Independent Director of Greif, Inc. since August 31, 2004 and Finning International Inc. since November 1, 2016. She has been an Independent Director of Commercial Metals Company since 2014. She has been an Independent Director of Global Brass and Copper Holdings, Inc. since February 21, 2014. In her 23-year career with Inland, she received numerous promotions in the finance, treasury and accounting functions. She is actively involved in the Executives' Club of Chicago and The Chicago Financial Exchange. She is a Visiting Executive for the University of Illinois and volunteers with several charitable organizations in the Chicago area. Ms. Avril has an MBA in Finance from the University of Chicago and B.S. in Accounting from the University of Illinois in Champaign.Read Full Background




